{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Decriminalise all drug possession for personal use & fund support",
        "additional_details": "We believe criminalising drug use wastes billions, fuels mass incarceration, and worsens public health. We think countries like Portugal have shown that treating addiction as a health issue, not a crime, can reduce overdoses, disease, and drug-related crime. We believe punishment fails to address the root causes, and a health-first approach can save money, improve safety, and restore dignity. We believe decriminalisation is a humane, cost-effective path forward.",
        "background": "We urge the government to decriminalise all drug possession for personal use and shift resources to health-based solutions. We believe criminalisation has failed and it\u2019s time for a new approach. We want the Government to fund addiction treatment, mental health support, and education.",
